<div class="lang-en">
<section id="overview">
  <h2>How Animal Personality Traits Work</h2>
  <p>Each of the twelve <a href="/zodiac/">Chinese zodiac animals</a> carries a distinct personality archetype rooted in centuries of observation and classical texts. These are not arbitrary assignments &mdash; each animal's traits derive from its position in the cycle, its associated <a href="/wuxing/">element</a>, compass direction, season, and time of day.</p>
  <p>The animal of your birth year represents your <strong>social personality</strong> &mdash; how others perceive you and how you interact with the world at large. In <a href="/bazi/">BaZi</a> analysis, the year pillar governs your relationship with society, grandparents, and early childhood influences. It is the most public of the four pillars, which is why zodiac animals are so widely recognised.</p>
  <p>Remember that the <a href="/chinese-zodiac-elements-guide/">Five Elements</a> modify these base traits significantly. A Water Rat and a Fire Rat share the Rat foundation but express it differently.</p>
</section>
</div>
<div class="lang-tc">
<section id="overview">
  <h2>生肖性格特徵的運作方式</h2>
  <p>十二<a href="/zodiac/">生肖動物</a>各自承載著獨特的性格原型，植根於數百年的觀察與經典文獻。這些並非隨意賦予——每種動物的特徵源於其在生肖週期中的位置、所屬<a href="/wuxing/">五行</a>、方位、季節和時辰。</p>
  <p>出生年的動物代表你的<strong>社會性格</strong>——即他人如何看待你，以及你如何與外界互動。在<a href="/bazi/">八字</a>分析中，年柱主宰你與社會、祖父母及幼年影響的關係。年柱是四柱中最公開的一柱，這也是生肖廣為人知的原因。</p>
  <p>請記住，<a href="/chinese-zodiac-elements-guide/">五行</a>會顯著改變這些基本特質。水鼠與火鼠雖共享鼠的基礎，但表現方式截然不同。</p>
</section>
</div>
